  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I gladly followed along, as a young person, and was impressed by what Hitler said, but I never attended any conferences, or any [CLEARS THROAT] secret meetings, nor did I see any secret documents, which indicated the plans for the occupation of Austria, or for [CLEARS THROAT] the invasion of Poland, or any of the other aggressive acts.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we never could prove that he did see those.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had a lawyer by the name of Dr.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sauter, S-A-U-T-E-R, who also defended the defendant, Von Ribbentrop, for a time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But Ribbentrop didn't like him, because Sauter wouldn't perform exactly as Ribbentrop wanted him to.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so Ribbentrop got another lawyer, and then still another lawyer.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] But Sauter stayed on as the attorney to-- as the main defense attorney for Schirach.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Sauter was one of the older lawyers who still had left in him some residues of the practice of the law before the Nazis came to power.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was also true of [CLEARS THROAT] Rudolph Dix, who was the counsel for Schacht, who undoubtedly, as the-- he had been the president of the German Bar Association before the Nazis came to power.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And within months after the Nazis came to power, he [CLEARS THROAT] signed a document, more or less, turning over the German Bar Association to the German Nazi group, which was led by the defendant, Hans Frank.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Schirach was found [CLEARS THROAT] not guilty on count one, the conspiracy count.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
